Regarding volumes, use this example volume id: vol-0F1941FF (or vol_0F1941FF on filer).

filer output:

{code}
vol_0F1941FF aggr1_SAS_04 online     RW       1.26GB     1.26GB    0%
{code}

The SC logs:

{code}
Thu Nov 21 18:21:28 2013 ERROR [NetappAdapter:Eucalyptus.storage.class java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker#556] [com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.san.netapp.NetappAdapter.destroyLun(NetappAdapter.java):303] #destroyLun#/vol/vol_0F1941FF/lun1: Failed to destroy lun
com.netapp.nmsdk.ApiExecutionException: Connection timed out
{code}

In this case connection to filer times out (refused by filer?).

This is a bad example however, if you look at filer output it is one of the only volumes with nothing in it (0% used).

The issue is with other volumes which are 1.26GB in size but cannot be traced at all in the SC logs.
